This paper deals with motion planning and control, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of optimization techniques such as sum-of-squares programming (SOS) suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the focus on safety and feasibility suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SD).
